.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-env-create - Create a new BC environment


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock env create [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a new BC environment.

.PP
When --version / --country / --region are all omitted and stdin is a terminal,
the CLI fetches fast configs (versions with pre-built VM images) across all
regions and prompts you to pick one - avoiding the ~78 min image build that
happens when no pre-built image exists.

.PP
Pass the flags explicitly to skip the picker (scripts, CI, agent use).

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  4   rate-limited
  10  provisioning failed (only with --wait and env status=failed)


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--country\fP=""
	Country localisation (e.g. au, us, gb)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for create

.PP
\fB--multi-tenant\fP[=true]
	Multi-tenant mode

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	Environment name

.PP
\fB--region\fP=""
	Azure region

.PP
\fB--type\fP="sandbox"
	Environment type: sandbox or onprem

.PP
\fB--version\fP=""
	BC version (e.g. 25.5)

.PP
\fB--wait\fP[=false]
	Block until running or failed

.PP
\fB--wait-timeout\fP=0s
	Max time to wait (default: 30m)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock env create
  bcdock env create --name my-env --version 25.5 --country au --region westus2
  bcdock env create --name my-env --version 25.5 --country au --region westus2 --wait
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-env(1)\fP
